The paper deals with classification in data streams, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper proposes a framework that aims to recognize recurring concepts and reuse a classifier trained previously, which involves meta-learning and adaptation, falling under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the problem of concept drift, which is a common issue in data streams and falls under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper uses synthetic and real-world datasets, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
